  <front>
    <title>Bi-directional LSPs for classical MPLS</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-dube-bidirectional-lsp-01"/>
    <author initials="R." surname="Dube" fullname="Rohit Dube">
      <organization>Xebeo Communications</organization>
    </author>
    <author initials="M." surname="Costa" fullname="Michele Costa">
      <organization>Xebeo Communications</organization>
    </author>
    <date day="25" month="July" year="2003"/>
    <abstract>
      <t>This memo proposes extensions to support bi-directional LSPs for
classical MPLS. Specifically RSVP-TE is extended with objects 
similar to those in GMPLS to allow establishment of bi-directional 
LSPs for MPLS networks.</t>
    </abstract>
  </front>
